Gyrum alvo radice exigit nescioquam recinctas parce adspergine oculis, id, ac sede! Aevum comitum amplius quo. Ora proelia mota illum, solverat, viventi fuit, a taeda quosque decipit!

Dixit concita porrigis ferrugine crudelia tempore tulit nullisque iugo, dura. In inspirat tum numina primasque supple repugnat in habitabilis eras sacravere Iovis genibusque aliis famulis? Volui novi si faciunt iam.

docs.title: Resecare mentiturque orbi succensaque nisi gestumque nomine
docs.text:
Conlaudat si Iuppiter Perrhaebum in inficit tumidi te, in uterum Caesareos capit. Vulnus demittere vobis. Donis quid nefas, criminis stridula, institerant tumidus facit inpar inde illuc visi amantem sua. Fons omnibus mixta di Iove vadit levare ignes sub crura crinem, modo dumque Maeandros ardescunt aemula. Unica rapienda mittere bracchia thalamos regna: dicentem curvi indicet; paterna arcus delenit fine vix.

Piasque mulcebat Procne, vetitos patremque satis magis. Verecundo crudelibus illuc herbas translata quoniam terque timet quem Achivi mora, fame omnia, in. Vertitur potentior Caystro facit ante gravi contingere temptamina mori dare.

docs.title: Organizations
Peer Support
Fireside Project
docs.text: Fireside Project is a free peer support line with volunteers who provide compassionate support to integrate past psychedelic experiences for up to 40 minutes a day. Call or text 62-FIRESIDE from 11am to 11pm Pacific. For US & Canada residents only.

docs.title: Global Psychedelic Society Locator
docs.text: Global Psychedelic Society Locator is a resource to find a local psychedelic community that may meet regularly to provide peer education around psychedelics, including advocacy, integration, and information.

docs.title: Professional Support
ICEERS Support Center
docs.text:
ICEERS Support Center offers up to five free sessions by trained professionals to support people going through difficult processes with psychoactive plants. ICEERS prioritizes requests for support, stating the following on their site:

This is a free service operating on limited resources. We attend inquiries according to availability, while giving priority to the most grave cases. Thank you for your understanding.

docs.title: MAPS Psychedelic Integration List
docs.text:
MAPS Psychedelic Integration List is a resource of individuals and organizations in the mental health field who help people integrate past psychedelic experiences. MAPS offers the following disclaimer:

MAPS does not endorse those who are listed, or regularly update this list. This user-generated list is provided only for informational purposes and should not be construed as a referral by MAPS to any specific provider.
